# Devus – Cline AI Rules
# Automatically loaded by Cline (formerly Claude Dev) in VS Code.

## Tech Stack
React 18, TypeScript, Vite 5, Bun, Tailwind CSS 3.4, Framer Motion 12, Supabase (Lovable Cloud), React Router 6, React Query 5, Zod 3.

## Import Rules
- ALWAYS use `@/` alias. Never relative `../../`.
- Supabase client: `import { supabase } from "@/integrations/supabase/client"`

## Design System (STRICT)
- All colors via HSL CSS variables in `src/index.css` and `tailwind.config.ts`.
- Use semantic tokens: `bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `border-muted`, `bg-surface`, etc.
- NEVER hardcode colors (`#hex`, `rgb()`, `text-white`, `bg-black`).
- Fonts: Sora (display), Inter (body), JetBrains Mono (code).

## Component Rules
- PascalCase filenames, named exports, one component per file.
- Use shadcn/ui from `src/components/ui/` as base primitives.
- Animations: Framer Motion only.

## State
- Auth → `useAuth()` from `@/contexts/AuthContext`
- Server data → React Query hooks
- Tool catalog → `@/lib/data.ts` and `@/lib/types.ts`

## Read-Only Files (NEVER edit)
- `src/integrations/supabase/client.ts`
- `src/integrations/supabase/types.ts`
- `supabase/config.toml`
- `.env`

## Backend / Supabase
- Edge functions: `supabase/functions/<name>/index.ts` (Deno)
- Always add RLS policies to new tables.
- User roles in separate `user_roles` table, never on profiles.
- No anonymous signups.

## Dependencies
- Install with `bun add`. Verify with Context7 MCP first.
- Don't duplicate existing package functionality.

## Prohibited
- Hardcoded colors in components
- localStorage for auth/roles
- API keys in source code
- Editing auto-generated Supabase files
- Relative import paths
